<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4541&amp;p=7046#p7046"><![CDATA[
&lt;div&gt;s doesn't hold any more semantic value than tables. The screen reader probably would ignore empty &lt;div&gt;. The real answer is to use elements supposed to work like such. without all those lol &lt;div&gt;s.<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;label&gt;Title:<br />&lt;select&gt;&lt;option&gt;&lt;/option&gt;<br />&lt;option&gt;Dr&lt;/option&gt;<br />&lt;option&gt;Miss&lt;/option&gt;<br />&lt;option&gt;Mr&lt;/option&gt;<br />&lt;option&gt;Mrs&lt;/option&gt;<br />&lt;option&gt;Ms&lt;/option&gt;&lt;/select&gt;&lt;/label&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />And use CSS with it:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>label {width:300px; display:block; text-align:right}<br />label select, label input {width:150px}</code></dd></dl><br /><br />Everybody is happy <img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1881">GlitchMr</a> — Fri Apr 15, 2011 6:17 am</p><hr />
